FBIS4-11198 "drlat079_f_94012" FBIS-LAT-94-079 Daily Report 25 Apr 1994 CENTRAL AMERICA El Salvador Zamora Admits Defeat Zamora Admits Defeat PA2504030194 San Salvador Radio Cadena YSKL in Spanish 0214 GMT 25 Apr 94 PA2504030194 San Salvador Radio Cadena YSKL Spanish BFN [Report from the Ramada Inn Hotel in San Salvador by Angel Iraheta -- live] [Text] [Iraheta] We are here at the Ramada Inn Hotel, where Dr. Ruben Zamora has just confirmed that he telephoned presidential candidate Dr. Armando Calderon Sol to congratulate him. Let us listen to Dr. Ruben Zamora, presidential candidate of the leftist coalition made up of the Farabundo Marti National Liberation Front, Democratic Convergence, and National Revolutionary Movement: [Zamora, in progress] .... dignity. First we want to thank all Salvadorans who voted for us and tell them that their wishes for change and a better way of life are still alive. We will continue working toward those things. [Words indistinct] for the force attained through these electoral events to fulfill our commitment and to continue working hard first for full compliance with the peace agreements, and second to defend and promote the interests of the majority in our country to attain a true state of development with justice and (?happiness) for all Salvadorans. We have reached specific agreements, such as the agreement on electoral reform, with the Nationalist Republican Alliance and its candidate. We want to voice our willingness to immediately begin the electoral reforms that our country needs so much. We are certain that Dr. Armando Calderon Sol will keep his campaign promises. Thank you for your attention.
